---
const repoUrl = "https://github.com/previewctl/previewctl-cli";
const waitlistUrl = `${repoUrl}/issues/new?title=Cloud%20PR%20Preview%20Waitlist&body=Please%20add%20me%20to%20the%20waitlist.%0A%0AGitHub%20org%2Frepo%3A%20%0ATeam%20size%3A%20%0AUse%20case%3A%20`;
const roadmapUrl = `${repoUrl}/issues?q=is%3Aissue%20cloud%20preview`;
---

<section class="coming-soon" aria-labelledby="cloud-preview-heading">
  <div class="coming-soon-header">
    <p class="coming-soon-kicker">Coming Soon</p>
    <h2 id="cloud-preview-heading">Cloud PR previews for every pull request</h2>
    <p>
      We are building a hosted workflow that detects new PRs, spins up a preview
      environment, and comments back with a live URL.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="coming-soon-flow" role="list" aria-label="Cloud preview workflow">
    <div class="flow-step" role="listitem">
      <span class="flow-index">1</span>
      <p>PR is opened in GitHub.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flow-step" role="listitem">
      <span class="flow-index">2</span>
      <p>Bot comments: preview environment is in progress.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flow-step" role="listitem">
      <span class="flow-index">3</span>
      <p>We build and deploy an isolated environment.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flow-step" role="listitem">
      <span class="flow-index">4</span>
      <p>Bot updates the PR with the preview URL.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="coming-soon-actions">
    <a href={waitlistUrl} class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
      Join the Waitlist
    </a>
    <a href={roadmapUrl} class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
      Track Progress
    </a>
  </div>
  <p class="coming-soon-note">
    Early access will roll out in batches. Tell us your repo size and team setup
    so we can prioritize onboarding.
  </p>
</section>
